{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/strokeshapeview\/geometrygroup()"]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ItemView"},{"type":"text","text":" may be added and removed at different times the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/StrokeShapeView"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/StrokeShapeView\/geometryGroup()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","symbolKind":"method","remoteSource":{"fileName":"RendererEffect.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L304"},"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":